==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: hip
<hw>hip</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Aware of the latest ideas,
trends, fashions, and developments in popular music and entertainment
culture; not square; -- same as <altname>hep</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tuned in.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Aware of the latest fashions and behaving as
expected socially, especially in clothing style and musical taste;
exhibiting an air of casual sophistication; cool; with it; -- used
mostly among young people in the teens to twenties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hipbone</ent>⟦br⟧
